article.headline: Marist 76, Siena 74
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Adam Kemp scored 24 points and grabbed 14 rebounds to lead Marist to a 76-74 victory over Siena on Friday night in a Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference game. Kemp scored seven times on dunks for the Red Foxes (9-20, 5-12). Marist went ahead to stay, 72-70, on Jay Bowie's layup with 56 seconds left. The Saints (7-22, 4-13) had two chances to tie it, but Davis Martens missed the back end of a 1-and-1 with 27 seconds left and Evan Hymes missed a 3-pointer with 20 on the clock. Devin Price scored 18 points for the Red Foxes and Chavaughn Lewis added 17. Trenity Burdine scored a career-high 17 points for Siena, and O.D. Anosike had 16 points and nine rebounds. Anosike, the Saints' lone senior, had to leave his final home game with dehydration after his tying three-point play with 3:18 left. He returned briefly at the 54-second mark.
